cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this benchmark, dataset, or harness, please cite the following technical report."
type: software
title: "Kantesti AI Engine (2.78T) — Blood Test Benchmark V11"
abstract: >-
  A pre-registered, rubric-based clinical validation of the Kantesti AI Engine
  (version 2.78T) on 15 anonymised blood test cases across seven medical
  specialties, including two hyperdiagnosis trap cases. The engine achieved a
  composite score of 0.9912 (99.12%) with zero hyperdiagnosis false-positives
  on both trap cases. The full evaluation harness is released under the MIT
  licence.
